comments: Marginal contact occurs when Ball (NOP) moves into McConnell's (IND) path on the perimeter.
Any contact by Holiday (IND) during Ingram's (NOP) jump shot attempt is marginal.
McConnell (IND) cleanly deflects the ball away from Adams (NOP) during the rebound.
Bitadze (IND) does not establish himself in a screening position in Bledsoe's (NOP) path and he initiates contact with Bledsoe from a wide stance.
Turner (IND) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Williamson (NOP) after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Turner (IND) and Ball (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Adams (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in McConnell's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Holiday (IND) contests the jump shot attempt by Ingram (NOP) and any contact that occurs is marginal.
Turner (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Ball's (NOP) path and does not deliver contact.
Ingram (NOP) and Holiday (IND) engage and disengage with one another off ball prior to the inbound pass.
Adams (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Holiday (IND) places his arm to Ingram's (IND) side and removes it at the start of his upward shooting motion.
Turner (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Bledsoe's (NOP) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
A 24 second violation is correctly called.
Hart NOP) reaches across Holiday's (IND) body during his drive and delivers contact that affects his SQBR.
Ball (NOP) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as body contact occurs during Turner's (IND) driving shot attempt.
Holiday (IND) makes incidental leg to leg contact with Hart (NOP) as Hart's momentum carries him backwards and to the floor.
